message: "If you use CANYON in your research, please cite this repository."
title: "CANYON: A framework for mechanistic and behavioural evaluation of semantic grounding in LLMs"
authors:
  - family-names: Urosevic
    given-names: Predrag
    orcid: ""
    affiliation: ""
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-06-07
url: "https://github.com/pedjaurosevic/canyon"
repository-code: "https://github.com/pedjaurosevic/canyon"
license: MIT
type: software
keywords:
  - LLM semantic grounding
  - world models
  - stochastic parrot
  - mechanistic interpretability
  - multilingual benchmark
  - counterfactual reasoning
  - latent space drift
abstract: >
  CANYON is an open-source research harness and benchmark designed to test
  Geoffrey Hinton's hypothesis about functional understanding and internal
  world models in large language models (LLMs). It behaviourally scores models
  on counterfactual physics, syntactic amphiboly, and oxymoronic humour across
  six languages (EN, ZH, JA, RU, DE, ES), and mechanistically measures
  latent-space semantic drift via hidden-state activations. Results are
  expressed as a Stochastic Parrot Index (SPI).
